            <h3>Step 02 - Mounting the Motor</h3>
            <p><ul>
                <li>Cut a piece of 3mm ply-wood to a height of 15.5" and width of 3".  </li>
                <li>Find the motor mount that comes with the brushless motor.<br>
                    Trace the mount's holes in the middle of the ply-wood strip.</li>
                <li>Drill the traced holes. The middle hole must have a diameter of 6mm, allowing the motor axle to spin freely. The four mounting holes must have a diameter of 4mm.</li>
                <li>Attach the mount to the motor - screws are given with the motor to fasten the mount. <br>
                    Screw the mounted motor to the plywood using the holes we've drilled earlier. use nuts on the other end to properly secure the mount.
                </li>
            </ul></p>
        </div>
