            <h3>Step 03 - Joining the electronics and securing them</h3>
            <p>Connect the bullet connectors on the motor to the ESC's bullet holes. <br>
                Connect the ESC's JR Connector to the Servo Tester. The knob on the servo tester will control the power to the motor.
                <br>
                When you're running the motor, connect the other end of the ESC to the battery. At all other times, the connection to the battery must not be made. 
            </p>
            <p>The electronics must be secured to the rear of the plywood strip, away from the face of the motor. Orientations vary according to the length of your wires. An example is shown in the image.
                Once you've found the orientation, secure the components with fibre-glass tape - make sure nothing is in line of the propeller. 
            </p>
